<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="509" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/864.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-02">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 2, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your February 28. Referring to last statement of Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs, you are instructed to inform him that this Government earnestly
                            desires prompt signing of protocol of arbitration, and issuance of
                            instructions for vise of passports of American citizens of Syrian origin
                            naturalized prior to anti-Syrian law of 1903.<note n="3" xml:id="d509fn3">
                                <ref target="frus1913#pg_575">For. Rel. 1913, pp. 575</ref>–<ref target="frus1913#pg_589">589</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>